reviews.text: First time here and we loved it. Food was great in my opinion. Everything tasted and looked fresh. Honestly might have been one of the best burgers I‚Äôve had in a while. Would definitely eat here again. Picture looks a little weird but it was better in person.
The wings on my burger were fantastic delicious. The fries are okay, too. Clean environment.

Tom was incredibly kind and informed me about their late Friday and Saturday hours. The food was amazing too and the Tex-Mex burger was more Mex than Tex and I absolutely LOVED it!! If you can‚Äôt handle the spice though, don‚Äôt get it ‚ò∫Ô∏è

My work partner and I were starving and wanted somewhere with good burgers. These reviews were misleading. No one said these burgers were flame-grilled like Burger King and completely unseasoned. Cajun fries had no salt and the catfish was also unseasoned. The guy who took our orders was nice, but he was kinda weird and started while we ate. Almost like he was seeing if we liked the food. Trust me, it‚Äôs beyond mediocre. If you like or must eat unseasoned food, this might be a place for you. But by NO means should this pop up in Google‚Äôs answers when one searches best burgers in Dallas. No thank you. Lemon pepper wings were the best thing and were about a 3.5 out of 5. Fried pickles were a 1 with nasty batter. Everything was made fresh though. However, these reviews and pictures are deceiving, and the food is tasteless and expensive.

Came because it was open late and its rating. It's a college area and it services Highland Park but seriously. The burger itself was decently priced especially if it's prime rib. How are frozen tater tots and a small drink the same price? Doubled the total for what? It's not about the money. There are a dozen places we go that's about 20+ a person for a burger with side and don't always even include the drink. You still want It to make sense. The quality wasn't there.

No excuses. I make burgers with prime rib or any other manner of beef all the time. Never come out this dry and hard.

Meat was over pressed. There is no space for the fats and makes the meat dense. Not juicey like it should be. The  bread and toppings were good but the brick of meat in the center really threw it off. Service was flat. The freezer tots were overcooked. There was some kind of burn (not about temperature) flavor to them. Maybe double cooked? Too many places in the area I would rather get food.

The wings would have to be more than spectacular (there was an issue so we didn't get them) My wife eats Jack in the Box! Her bar is low, she loves burgers. This is a definant no, thank you.

detailedReviews.text: I was hungry and saw this place was open late so I decided to try this place. The wings were ok especially the fact that it was 1145pm and they were hot. But the customer service was terrible. The gentleman working the front was not approachable and when I asked for suggestions about customer favorites he gave a short rude answer. I asked for all flats and his response was I don't think they can do it but he never checked to see. After I got my wings and went to my car I noticed he did not place my ranch in my bag when I got out the car in the cold to get the ranch he ask me about 3 times if I'm sure I didn't have it in box or bag and I was definitely sure. The place was literally empty but his energy gave the vibe that they were busy. I ate in car and for it to be a after hours restaurant I saw no customers come in so it's strange that he was so rude. I  wouldn't recommend this place.

detailedReviews.author: Mister Myself
detailedReviews.text:
Came because it was open late and its rating. It's a college area and it services Highland Park but seriously. The burger itself was decently priced especially if it's prime rib. How are frozen tater tots and a small drink the same price? Doubled the total for what? It's not about the money. There are a dozen places we go that's about 20+ a person for a burger with side and don't always even include the drink. You still want It to make sense. The quality wasn't there.

No excuses. I make burgers with prime rib or any other manner of beef all the time. Never come out this dry and hard.

Meat was over pressed. There is no space for the fats and makes the meat dense. Not juicey like it should be. The  bread and toppings were good but the brick of meat in the center really threw it off. Service was flat. The freezer tots were overcooked. There was some kind of burn (not about temperature) flavor to them. Maybe double cooked? Too many places in the area I would rather get food.

The wings would have to be more than spectacular (there was an issue so we didn't get them) My wife eats Jack in the Box! Her bar is low, she loves burgers. This is a definant no, thank you.

detailedReviews.text: My husband and I went to this burger place based on reviews. The place was closing in 20 minutes. I usually don't go to places that are closing soon.i should have followed my 1st mind and left. The employee was outside smoking a cigarette at the door. At the time we didn't know he worked here. We order the employee came in and went straight to the back to cook our food, no handwriting. The meat was a frozen patty. The burger was the nastiest burger I've ever eaten. We are from Denver and we know Dallas has goof food well a few years ago food was good here. I couldn't eat the burger the little bit I ate made me extremely sick!!!! I will never go back to this place and will not suggest this place to anyone!!!

detailedReviews.author: ihategplayy
detailedReviews.text:
It's the little things. The food is good. I'm no foodie, but I like standard American fare and this is it. Enough about the food.... what motivated me to write a positive review is this little act of service they did.
I had a fairly large order....or rather a large SPECIFIC order. Anyone with younger kids knows how difficult it can be to order burgers to each person's wishes....get the order right or face to consequences of an angry kid that won't eat (and the subsequent "discussion" about being grateful for a burger in the first place). Anyway, I had FOUR DIFFERENT iterations of the same hamburger + three different wing orders. If you look at the picture I posted, you see that Solo Burger was SUPER THOUGHTFUL to pack each burger in a separate bag, number each bag, AND put the corresponding number next to the order on the ticket so you knew what was in each bag. I never even asked them to  do that. For those of you who don't know, the second great challenge after ordering food, is figuring out whose burger is whose when you get home. It's the little things, like this thoughtful act, which helps them stand out from the rest. Thank you solo burger.

detailedReviews.text:
I showed up to pick up for delivery, and the guy at the front was demanding I confirm my order before I even received the order. The staff was unprofessional and rude, so  I responded with a raised voice.

(Update) You should learn to read. I never had a problem confirming the order. The problem occurs when your representative wants me to confirm an order that I don't have possession of. If he handed me the order, then I can confirm that I have the order. I was in the process of verifying that the order was mine and accurate when he kept telling me to confirm the order. Check your cameras smart person.

detailedReviews.text: Super good, the best wings I've ever had. Really good sauce second or third best. Hole in the wall bar in DC holds the best sauce title for me...We were in the area for a dr's appointment for our daughter.. we needed to kill some time between appointments and had not eaten all day.  Stopped by Solo.. parking sucked ( not their fault). It was clean and smelled great inside . Ordered wings.I eat a lot of wings due to low carb diet.  They were so crispy I almost didn't eat them cuz I thought they were breaded.. lucky for me the owner took the time and asked if I didn't like em due to me asking for a To go box right after I tried one.  He let me know there was no breading!!!! and I went to town it was honestly kinda embarrassing! I looked like a baby eating his first birthday cake but I didn't care.. go get wings don't stop anywhere else on the way.

I typically go to wingstop and will continue to do so. The only part I enjoyed were the fries (handful amount that you pay extra for as a side).

I had half boneless wings (McDonald‚Äôs chicken nugget consistency)
& half bone-in wings (cooked well done and crispy; but the meat was so dry).

The buffalo sauce goes to mild -medium, which is fine.

I may try the burger next time, but that threw me off being that wings are in the title. üò£

So glad they have soda cans, so that the taste stays true.

Very sad wings and wasteful money spent.

I went today and instead of a good piece of chicken on my sandwich I got 2 over breaded tenders that breading was all I got. My bun was stale and falling apart. As much as I hate to say it I won‚Äôt go back. I spent $35 on a lunch that McDonalds would have been better and cheaper!
